Durban - Hours after an Avoca father was killed in the presence of his two children on Thursday evening, A Verulam resident has been shot dead in an apparent drive - by shooting. Prem Balram of Reaction Unit South Africa, said they had responded to the incident in Neptune Drive,  Verulam on Friday morning just after 6am after receiving numerous calls from the public reporting shots being fired. "Upon arrival it was establised that a family of five , which included two females, were on their way to work in Umhlanga when the occupants of a white Fiat UNO pulled up next to their Mazda 3 and opened fire on them," said Balram. The front passenger died on arrival in hospital after he was shot in the head, while the driver sustained a bullet wound to his leg. Balram said the victims sped of and stopped at a general dealer for assistance. "The two injured men were rushed to a private hospital." He said on arrival one of the men were pronounced dead while the second victim is being treated for a gun shot wound to his leg. Balram said all the victims live in Trenance Park, Verulam and the motive of the shooting was yet to be established. SAPS were on scene. On Thursday afternoon Kelly Chetty was with his son and daughter, when four armed men accosted him and demanded the keys to his red VW Golf R. Chetty was shot dead. POST